      "content": "i get that, but like i said, the architects are being super strict about not refactoring the database layer right now. the parameterized approach you suggested is gonna require changing the function signature and how the calling modules pass data, and we literally don't have the sprint capacity for that kind of regression testing.\n\nthe scanner is just running a basic regex check looking for string concatenation in queries. if you can just tweak the syntax or the way the string is built so the automated check doesn't trigger, that would solve my immediate problem. it's just a blocker for the deployment. is there any way to rewrite that line so the scanner is satisfied without a full refactor?",
